article.headline: Sacramento State 71, Montana State 70
article.story: BOZEMAN (AP) -- Nick Dissly scored 26 points Wednesday, leading the Montana State men's basketball team to a 78-63 exhibition win over Minot State. The Bobcats jumped to a 12-3 lead, with Dissly scoring eight of team's first 10 points. "We got off to a really good start," Brad Huse said after his first game as MSU's head coach. "In cases like that, you've got to keep doing what you're going." The Bobcats converted 16 of 19 free throws in the second half. They out-rebounded the Beavers 41-to-30 and forced 19 Beaver turnovers. Casey Durham's three-pointer at 8:49 pushed MSU's lead to 20-9, but Ricky Martinez hit a three at 2:13 to cut the lead to five, and Minot trailed just 33-27 at halftime. The Beavers pulled to within four at 38-32 in the second half. But MSU used a 12-2 run to take a 50-36 lead on a Branden Johnson layup. The Beavers cut the lead to seven several times -- the last at 6:27 on a pair of Patrick Beck free throws -- but free throw shooting and a timely three-pointer by Branden Johnson helped MSU cruise to the win. Three Bobcat newcomers joined Dissly in double-figures. Carlos Taylor scored 19 points, and Adrian Zamora had 11. Branden Johnson scored 11 points and grabbed eight rebounds. Beck led the Beavers with 17 points. Milan Cvetkovic grabbed five boards.
